<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1437,151,789]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
Remarks: This species has been recorded under numerous different names, and a high number of taxa previously considered as subspecies are now recognized as separate species (
<bibRefCitation author="Gerecke, R." box="[909,1075,511,537]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="141 - 378" refId="ref74237" refString="Gerecke, R. (2003) The water mites of the genus Atractides Koch, 1837 (Acari: Parasitengona: Hygrobatidae) in the western Palaearctic region: a revision. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 138, 141 - 378. https: // doi. org / 10.1046 / j. 1096 - 3642.06 - 0.00051. x" type="journal article" year="2003">Gerecke 2003</bibRefCitation>
). Further taxonomic research is required for a better understanding of its variability and distribution. As character states proposed for distinguishing females from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Sokolow" baseAuthorityYear="1940" box="[306,432,583,609]" class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Atractides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robustus">
<emphasis box="[306,432,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">A. robustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Gerecke, R." box="[474,648,583,609]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="141 - 378" refId="ref74237" refString="Gerecke, R. (2003) The water mites of the genus Atractides Koch, 1837 (Acari: Parasitengona: Hygrobatidae) in the western Palaearctic region: a revision. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 138, 141 - 378. https: // doi. org / 10.1046 / j. 1096 - 3642.06 - 0.00051. x" type="journal article" year="2003">Gerecke (2003)</bibRefCitation>
are weak and in many cases not suitable, records based exclusively on females remain always questionable, also in the list above. Females from sites or catchments where exclusively 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thor" authorityYear="1899" class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Atractides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nodipalpis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">A. nodipalpis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
males were found, were attributed to this species, vice versa for 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Sokolow" baseAuthorityYear="1940" box="[996,1122,655,681]" class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Atractides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robustus">
<emphasis box="[996,1122,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">A. robustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see there).
</paragraph>
